{
  "info": {
    "name": "Internet Stability Tracker API v2",
    "description": "Complete API collection for the Internet Stability Tracker v2 — community network monitoring platform.\n\n## Live Production URL\nAll requests default to the **live Fly.io deployment**:\n```\nhttps://backend-cold-butterfly-9535.fly.dev/api\n```\n\n## Switch to local dev\nChange the `base_url` collection variable to `http://localhost:8000/api`.\n\n## Swagger UI\n- **Production**: https://backend-cold-butterfly-9535.fly.dev/docs\n- **Local**: http://localhost:8000/docs\n\n## WebSocket\n```\nwss://backend-cold-butterfly-9535.fly.dev/api/ws/live\n```\n\n## Rate limits\n| Endpoint | Limit |\n|----------|-------|\n| `POST /test-now` | 5 req / 60 s per IP + per X-Client-ID |\n| `POST /reports` | 5 req / 60 s per IP + per X-Client-ID |\n| `DELETE /measurements` | 3 req / 60 s (admin key required) |\n| `GET /my-connection` | 10 req / 60 s per IP |\n| All others | 60 req / 60 s per IP |\n\n## New in v2\n- WebSocket live feed (`/ws/live`)\n- Browser bandwidth probe (`/bandwidth-probe`)\n- Congestion heatmap (`/congestion-heatmap`)\n- Week-over-week comparison (`/comparison`)\n- Anomaly detection (`/anomalies`)\n- Traceroute (`/traceroute`)\n- Multi-region latency (`/multi-region`)\n- Shareable snapshots (`/snapshots`)",
    "version": "2.0.0",
    "_postman_id": "ist-api-v2",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "https://backend-cold-butterfly-9535.fly.dev/api",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Production Fly.io URL. Change to http://localhost:8000/api for local development."
    },
    {
      "key": "report_id",
      "value": "1",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "ID of a community report — update after creating one via POST /reports"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/../health",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["..", "health"]
            },
            "description": "Returns service status, UTC timestamp, and current environment. Also accepts HEAD (used by Fly.io health probes)."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Healthy",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\"status\":\"healthy\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-11T14:54:29.327197+00:00\",\"environment\":\"production\"}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Speed Test",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Run speed test now",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/test-now?location=Kigali&lat=-1.9441&lon=30.0619",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["test-now"],
              "query": [
                {"key": "location", "value": "Kigali", "description": "Human-readable location label"},
                {"key": "lat", "value": "-1.9441", "description": "Latitude (-90 to 90)"},
                {"key": "lon", "value": "30.0619", "description": "Longitude (-180 to 180)"}
              ]
            },
            "description": "Triggers a real speed test (speedtest-cli). Takes 10–30 seconds to complete.\n\n**Rate limited**: 5 req / 60 s per IP.\n\nAll query params are optional."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Success",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\"id\":26,\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-11T14:55:00.123456\",\"download_speed\":187.2,\"upload_speed\":19.7,\"ping\":10.8,\"isp\":\"GVA-Canalbox\",\"location\":\"Kigali\",\"latitude\":-1.9441,\"longitude\":30.0619,\"is_outage\":false}"
            },
            {
              "name": "Rate Limited",
              "status": "Too Many Requests",
              "code": 429,
              "body": "{\"detail\":\"Too many requests — please slow down.\"}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Measurements",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List all measurements",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/measurements?skip=0&limit=50",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["measurements"],
              "query": [
                {"key": "skip",  "value": "0",  "description": "Offset (pagination)"},
                {"key": "limit", "value": "50", "description": "Max records returned (1–500)"}
              ]
            },
            "description": "Paginated list of speed test records, most recent first."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Recent measurements (24h)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/measurements/recent?hours=24",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["measurements", "recent"],
              "query": [
                {"key": "hours", "value": "24", "description": "Time window in hours (1–168). Use 168 for 7-day view."}
              ]
            },
            "description": "Measurements within the last N hours."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Clear all measurements",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/measurements",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["measurements"]
            },
            "description": "⚠️ IRREVERSIBLE — permanently deletes all speed test records and associated outage events."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Success",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\"deleted\":25,\"message\":\"All measurements cleared.\"}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Statistics",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Aggregated stats",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/stats?hours=24",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["stats"],
              "query": [
                {"key": "hours", "value": "24", "description": "Time window in hours (1–168)"}
              ]
            },
            "description": "Total tests, outage count, uptime %, average download / upload / ping for the time window."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Success",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\"total_tests\":10,\"total_outages\":0,\"uptime_percentage\":100.0,\"avg_download_mbps\":187.5,\"avg_upload_mbps\":19.8,\"avg_ping_ms\":10.9,\"last_test_at\":\"2026-03-11T14:55:00\",\"hours\":24}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Network Quality Score",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/quality-score?hours=24",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["quality-score"],
              "query": [
                {"key": "hours", "value": "24", "description": "Time window in hours (1–168)"}
              ]
            },
            "description": "Composite 0–100 quality score with letter grade (A+/A/B/C/D/F).\n\n**Scoring formula**:\n- Speed score: 0–40 pts (download vs 200 Mbps benchmark)\n- Upload score: 0–20 pts (upload vs 50 Mbps)\n- Ping score: 0–20 pts (lower ping = higher score)\n- Uptime score: 0–20 pts (uptime % contribution)\n\n**Grades**: A+ ≥95, A ≥85, B ≥70, C ≥55, D ≥40, F <40"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Score A",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\"score\":81.5,\"grade\":\"A\",\"label\":\"Very Good\",\"breakdown\":{\"speed_score\":36.5,\"upload_score\":6.7,\"ping_score\":18.4,\"uptime_score\":20.0,\"avg_download\":91.13,\"avg_upload\":16.8,\"avg_ping\":24.54,\"uptime_pct\":100.0},\"hours\":24}"
            },
            {
              "name": "No data",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\"score\":0,\"grade\":\"N/A\",\"label\":\"No Data\",\"breakdown\":{},\"hours\":24}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Global Status",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/status",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["status"]
            },
            "description": "Overall platform status: `healthy` / `degraded` / `outage`.\n\nIncludes active outage count, open community reports, 24h averages, and a 7-day daily summary used by the Status Page."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Healthy",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\"status\":\"healthy\",\"active_outages\":0,\"open_reports\":0,\"avg_download_24h\":91.13,\"uptime_pct_24h\":100.0,\"total_measurements_7d\":10,\"daily_summary\":[{\"date\":\"2026-03-11\",\"tests\":2,\"outages\":0,\"uptime_pct\":100.0,\"avg_download\":91.13}],\"checked_at\":\"2026-03-11T18:31:22.951925\"}"
            },
            {
              "name": "Degraded",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\"status\":\"degraded\",\"active_outages\":1,\"open_reports\":3,\"avg_download_24h\":12.5,\"uptime_pct_24h\":87.0,\"total_measurements_7d\":48,\"daily_summary\":[],\"checked_at\":\"2026-03-11T19:00:00.000000\"}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Alerts",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Current alert status",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/alerts",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["alerts"]
            },
            "description": "Whether there is an active outage right now, plus the 48-hour outage count and recent events."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "All clear",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\"current_outage\":false,\"outage_count_48h\":0,\"recent_outages\":[]}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Outage Confidence Score",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/outage-confidence",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["outage-confidence"]
            },
            "description": "Smart confidence score (0–100%) for whether the current network state is a real outage vs a brief blip.\n\nFactors:\n- Recent measurement speeds vs threshold\n- Community report density in the last hour\n- Number of consecutive low-speed readings"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "No outage",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\"confidence\":0,\"is_likely_outage\":false,\"factors\":{\"speed_factor\":0,\"report_factor\":0,\"consecutive_factor\":0},\"recent_measurements\":5,\"recent_reports\":0}"
            },
            {
              "name": "High confidence outage",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\"confidence\":87,\"is_likely_outage\":true,\"factors\":{\"speed_factor\":50,\"report_factor\":22,\"consecutive_factor\":15},\"recent_measurements\":8,\"recent_reports\":4}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Outages",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List outage measurements",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/outages?limit=50",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["outages"],
              "query": [
                {"key": "limit", "value": "50", "description": "Max records (1–200)"}
              ]
            },
            "description": "Individual speed test records where `is_outage=true`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Outage event log",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/outage-events?limit=50&resolved_only=false",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["outage-events"],
              "query": [
                {"key": "limit",         "value": "50",    "description": "Max records (1–200)"},
                {"key": "resolved_only", "value": "false", "description": "true = only resolved events"}
              ]
            },
            "description": "Structured outage events with computed `duration_minutes` and `severity` (critical / high / medium)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Timeline",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/timeline?days=30",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["timeline"],
              "query": [
                {"key": "days", "value": "30", "description": "Number of days to look back (1–60)"}
              ]
            },
            "description": "Chronological event timeline grouped by date.\n\nEvent types: `outage` (red), `degradation` (orange), `recovery` (green).\n\nUsed by the Timeline page — shows duration, avg speed, severity badge, and resolved status."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Success",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\"days\":30,\"total_events\":3,\"events\":[{\"id\":1,\"type\":\"outage\",\"severity\":\"critical\",\"started_at\":\"2026-03-10T08:00:00\",\"ended_at\":\"2026-03-10T08:45:00\",\"duration_minutes\":45,\"isp\":\"MTN Rwanda\",\"location\":\"Kigali\",\"is_resolved\":true,\"avg_download\":0.1,\"date\":\"2026-03-10\"}]}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
